Gabon scored a late equalizing goal to hold Ghana to a 1-1 draw in their African Cup of Nations (AFCON) match at the Omnisport Ahmadou Ahidjo Stadium in Yaound√©, Cameroon. Andre Ayew had given Ghana the lead in the 18the minute before Jim Allevinah snatched a point for Gabon to deny the Black Stars their first win of the tournament. In the first face-off between both nations since 2011 and a first ever AFCON meeting, Ghana took the lead when Ayew drilled into the bottom corner after collecting a pass from Thomas Partey. The four-time AFCON winners continued to dominate but were denied by profligacy in the final third. Allevinah, who came on as a substitute, latched on to a pass before drilling into the bottom corner for a surprise leveler and they held on for a precious point. Gabon remain second on four points while Ghana secure their first point in two games. In earlier matches, Morocco defeated Comoros 2-0 to advance into the round of 16, while Senegal and Guinea played out a goalless draw in group B. Both nations would fight for the right to win the group in the final group games. RESULTS 